/** \mainpage Userguide

ZZACWT is a Morse Code (aka CW) training application for amateur radio operators.
It provides the following functionality:
- Generate random Morse code sequences for practice.
- Allows the speed and spacing model (eg Farnsworth) to be configured.
- Allows the pitch of the generated Morse code to be configured.
- Adds "disturbances" to the generated Morse code to simulate real-world conditions.
- Displays the generated text and allows the user to enter what they heard for comparison.	

